items.name: Knox 3D Pen for 3D Drawing, Printing and Doodling with LCD Screen (Blue)
items.longDescription: Model: KN-3DPENB. <br>Get ready to have a ton of fun with the Knox 3D Printing Pen. It's great for both kids and adults who are into arts & crafts, drawing or just making. If you haven't heard of them before, 3D printing pens are devices that you hold and use just like a pen or marker. Except instead of ink, you draw in plastic! You can draw a line from your table straight into the air! But it's more than just drawing. Since it's plastic, you can build with it too! It's like magic and you're only limited by your imagination in what you can create.<br>Some examples of what you can make include drawing a flat picture in plastic. Like a sign, nametag or picture of your own design. You can print panels to a 3D structure and use more printed plastic to "glue" those sides together, making larger & more complex ideas come to life. You can even draw freeform in the air and make little figurines of anything you can dream up.<br>This printing pen uses either PLA or ABS filament and comes with a starter pack to get you going right out of the box. You simply plug in the pen, turn it on and feed the plastic filament into the back of the pen. The pen does the rest by pulling in and heating the plastic. With the press of a button a steady stream of plastic will come out of the nozzle. Just like a box of crayons, you can swap out different filaments to change the color of your design easily. When not in use, just put it back into the included holder.<br><br><b>Specifications:</b><br>Compatible with PLA or ABS Filament (we recommend the use of Knox branded filament)<br>Diameter of Material - 1.75mm<br>Nozzle Hole Size - 0.7mm<br>Melting Temp. (ABS) - 230C/446F<br>Melting Temp. (PLA) - 170C/338F<br>Unit Size - 7.2" x 1.2" x 1.8"<br>Unit Weight - 2.1 oz.<br><br><b>Key Feature:</b><br>Draw 3D Objects in Plastic<br>Built-in LCD Display<br>Compatible with ABS or PLA Filament<br>Comfortable Design<br>Forward & Reverse Buttons<br><br><b>In Box</b> <br>•Knox 3D Printing Pen with LCD Screen <br>•Pen Holder <br>•Filament Starter Pack (Colors May Vary) <br>•AC Power Supply <br>•Product Manual

items.name: Revival
items.shortDescription: "In a small New England town over half a century ago, a boy is playing with his new toy soldiers in the dirt in front of his house when a shadow falls over him. He looks up to see a striking man, the new minister, Jamie learns later, who with his beautiful wife, will transform the church and the town. The men and boys are a bit in love with Mrs. Jacobs; the women and girls, with the Reverend Jacobs--including Jamie's sisters and mother. Then tragedy strikes, and this charismatic preacher curses God, and is banished from the shocked town. Jamie has demons of his own. Wed to his guitar from age 13, he plays in bands across the country, running from his own family tragedies, losing one job after another when his addictions get the better of him. Decades later, sober and living a decent life, he and Reverend Charles Jacobs meet again in a pact beyond even the Devil's devising, and the many terrifying meanings of Revival are revealed. King imbues this spectacularly rich and dark novel with
items.longDescription: Years after a charismatic minister is banished in the wake of a faith-shattering tragedy, a heroin-addicted rock-and-roll guitarist from the same hometown reconnects with the man and forges a terrible pact. By the award-winning author of <i>Under the Dome</i>. 1.5 million first printing.

Additionally, PLA is a plant-based plastic, which means that it is biodegradable and gives off a slightly sweet odor, like roasting corn.<br><br>This 1 Kg spool features a thickness of 3.0mm �0.10mm, with a roundness variation of only 0.03mm. It has a nominal processing temperature of 185� C (365�F). Thickness and roundness factors are laser measured at the factory to ensure accuracy over the entire length of the filament.<br><br>The negatives of using PLA is that it is vulnerable to degradation from moisture, sunlight, and heat. items.name: Life Strategies for Teens: Exercises and Self-Tests to Help You Change Your Life
items.shortDescription: The best-selling author of Life Strategies for Teens introduces a series of exercises and activities designed to help teenagers understand and utilize the ten essential strategies designed to help teenagers take control of their lives and make the journey to adulthood a fulfilling one. Original. 125,000 first printing.
items.longDescription: FROM JAY MCGRAW, THE "NEW YORK TIMES" BESTSELLING AUTHOR OF "LIFE STRATEGIES FOR TEENS, " COMES A WORKBOOK CHOCK-FULL OF QUIZZES, TESTS, AND QUESTIONS TO HELP YOU FIGURE OUT WHO YOU ARE AND WHERE YOU ARE GOING. <br> So who are you? Are you the Teacher's Pet? The Slacker? The Jock? Do you let yourself be labeled by terms like these because it's easy, because you dress a certain way or listen to a certain rock band? Do you act the way you think others expect you to? Here's a more important question: Who are you really? <br> Jay McGraw's "New York Times" bestseller "Life Strategies for Teens" shows teens that Life Strategies are not just something for their parents, but that teens can use them to take over the driver's seat and steer their own lives as well. Jay speaks to teens as equals, and gives them the straight story he knows and has been through himself. <br> Now with the "Life Strategies for Teens Workbook, " Jay McGraw has created a fun-filled companion book to help teens work their way through the Life Strategies, and, in turn, through those tumultuous years between playing like a kid and acting as an adult. In the "Workbook, " Jay introduces a variety of entertaining quizzes, activities, and questions to help teens better answer the question of who they are. From figuring out the roles they play to determining the things they want to change about their lives, this is the perfect guide to showing teens the power of the Life Strategies, as well as the power of their own lives.
